<paragraph blockId="48.[151,1436,224,503]" box="[151,572,224,251]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,530,224,251]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Number of specimens recorded.</emphasis>
39.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="48.[151,1436,224,503]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,353,260,287]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Distribution.</emphasis>
Europe, thus far not recorded from the Iberian Peninsula. 
<collectingCountry box="[1020,1119,261,287]" name="Portugal" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Portugal</collectingCountry>
: five provinces, all over the country.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="48.[151,1436,224,503]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,300,333,359]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Ecology.</emphasis>
Recorded from 5 macrohabitat categories, lacking in dunes and mountainous biotopes, and clearly less frequently in forests as compared to others. In northwestern Europe, this eurytopic species is frequently collected in salt marshes, swamps and on the banks of various water bodies.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="48.[151,1436,224,503]" box="[199,754,440,467]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,337,440,467]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Rarity (%).</emphasis>
13.8 (common). Very common (FL).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="48.[151,1436,224,503]" box="[199,589,476,503]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,386,476,503]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Activity period.</emphasis>
April–November.
</paragraph>
